The paper discusses the design of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and their training, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The focus is on image classification tasks, which is a common application of CNNs in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the importance of network capacity and regularization, which are topics in neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of metrics to evaluate network performance, which is a topic in natural language processing (cs.CL).
